description:
The MetaWear C++ API is a C++ implementation of the MetaWear protocol designed to be used by higher level languages.  For Windows developers, the C++ API is compiled as a Windows Runtime Component on the Universal Windows Platform (UWP) eabling it to be used by both C# and C++/CX UWP projects.  This package includes:
    * .winmd file
    * .dll/.lib/.pri files for x86, x64, and ARM
    * C# wrappers defining the visible dll functions, structs, and enums
    * C++ header files

For C++ projects, the .targets file will automatically update the project properties to point to the C++ header files and .lib file for implicit linking.
summary: C++ implementation of the MetaWear protocol
title: MetaWear C++ API
